@startuml cluster_text_render_path_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Cluster Text Render Path Signal Flow\n(CGW -> IVI -> CLU)

participant "CGW\neffective alert gate" as CGW #FFF4CC
participant "IVI\nwarning text generator" as IVI #E8F0FE
participant "CLU\ncluster text owner" as CLU #E8F0FE

== Effective Alert Intake ==

activate CGW
CGW -> IVI : CoreState::selectedAlertEffectiveLevel / Type
CGW -> IVI : Core::timeoutClear
CGW -> IVI : Core::emergencyContext
CGW -> IVI : CoreState::emergencyIngressDirection / Eta
note right of CGW
Representative source seams
- selectedAlertEffectiveLevel
- selectedAlertEffectiveType
- timeoutClear
- emergency ingress context
end note
deactivate CGW

== IVI Warning Text Generation ==

activate IVI
CGW -> IVI : effective alert seams
IVI -> IVI : deriveWarningTextCode()
IVI -> IVI : warningTextCode
IVI -> CLU : frmClusterWarningMsg
IVI -> CLU : frmClusterNotifMsg
note right of IVI
Representative outputs
- frmClusterWarningMsg.WarningTextCode
- notif companion state
- UiRender::warningBeepState
end note
deactivate IVI

== CLU Cluster Text Ownership ==

activate CLU
IVI -> CLU : frmClusterWarningMsg
IVI -> CLU : frmClusterNotifMsg
CLU -> CLU : Cluster::warningTextCode = code
CLU -> CLU : clusterNotifType / clusterNotifPrio
deactivate CLU

note over CGW, CLU
Representative runtime chain
1. CGW exposes effective alert state
2. IVI converts alert context into WarningTextCode
3. IVI sends cluster warning + notification frames
4. CLU stores and displays Cluster::warningTextCode
end note

@enduml
